    "body": "### Problem\n\nit's kind of hard describing it with words, I hope the video is pretty clear about the problem, also sorry for the poor video quality, basically I can't delete anything _before_ the inlay hint virtual text\r\n\r\nhttps://github.com/neovim/neovim/assets/51160226/c85f7fdd-aa01-4a40-8540-310bf25e4ab4\r\n\r\n\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\n# Steps to reproduce using \"nvim -u minimal_init.lua\"\r\n\r\n```lua\r\n--- CHANGE THESE\r\nlocal pattern = \"rust\"\r\nlocal cmd = { \"rust-analyzer\" }\r\n-- Add files/folders here that indicate the root of a project\r\nlocal root_markers = { \".git\", \".editorconfig\", \"Cargo.toml\", \"Cargo.lock\" }\r\n-- Change to table with settings if required\r\nlocal settings = vim.empty_dict()\r\n\r\nvim.api.nvim_create_autocmd(\"FileType\", {\r\n\tpattern = pattern,\r\n\tcallback = function(args)\r\n\t\tlocal match = vim.fs.find(root_markers, { path = args.file, upward = true })[1]\r\n\t\tlocal root_dir = match and vim.fn.fnamemodify(match, \":p:h\") or nil\r\n\t\tvim.lsp.start({\r\n\t\t\tname = \"rust_analyzer\",\r\n\t\t\tcmd = cmd,\r\n\t\t\troot_dir = root_dir,\r\n\t\t\tsettings = settings,\r\n\t\t\ton_attach = function(client, bufnr)\r\n\t\t\t\tvim.lsp.buf.inlay_hint(bufnr, true)\r\n\t\t\tend,\r\n\t\t})\r\n\tend,\r\n})\r\n```\r\n\r\n<sup>Shamelessly stolen from #24068</sup>\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nI expect the characters behind the inlay hint virtual text to be deleted\n\n### Neovim version (nvim -v)\n\nNVIM v0.10.0-dev-541+g96b94f8d77\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nno\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nArch Linux\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nalacritty 0.12.1 (5fdfd47f)\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nalacritty\n\n### Installation\n\nneovim-git from Arch User Repository (AUR)",
